The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | New chairman
                                                                                                               New chairman
                              Arvind Jadhav                            
	New Delhi, April 30 (PTI): Arvind Jadhav, a 1978 batch IAS officer, has been appointed the full-time chairman and managing director of Air India, official sources said today.        
	Jadhav will take over from E.K. Bharat Bhushan, a joint secretary in the civil aviation ministry, who was asked to head the national carrier as an interim measure till a permanent CMD was appointed.        
	Jadhav, who is now principal secretary in the infrastructure development department of the Karnataka government, is also a member of the board of directors of the privatised Bangalore International Airport.                                                                                                                                        
